message.entry: Calling SIM2FI with 2 input arguments, the second argument must be a NUMERICTYPE object.
SIM2FI must have 2, 4, or 5 input arguments. You have entered 3.
Fixed-point data types in Simulink must have word lengths less than or equal to {0} bits.
A Fixed-Point Designer license is required to create a fi object with any data type other than double.
Cannot construct fi object; converting to double.
Integer array must be uint64 when wordLength is greater than 64.

For single-word code generation, the word length of the input integer array must be greater than or equal to the output word length. If the input word length is less than the output word length, use the typecast function to concatenate the input integer array to a bigger word length.
